node.text:
Today’s Flashback Friday is a glimpse into the digital classroom from this past week’s BUSINESS MASTERY VIRTUAL program! 👊🔥📈💥🙌 It was our final Business Mastery of the year, and we’re excited to be unleashing 2,500 business owners, entrepreneurs, artists and innovators out into the world! Armed with VISION, PURPOSE, and a new set of tools and strategies to help take their businesses to the next level 📈, these new #businessbootcamp grads are ready to create MASSIVE IMPACT in their businesses, communities, and for many – the world. 

It’s an amazing time to have a business – right in the middle of an economic WINTER. 🥶 Here’s the truth - the companies who are the most successful are the ones who can find a way to survive and THRIVE – especially in the midst of mass global fear and uncertainty. In business you either GROW or DIE. This is the time to STEP UP and grow! 🙌

We learned and grew all week together PLUS we joined hearts and raised $1.3 MILLION DOLLARS that will be used to save the lives of 2,600 women and children enslaved by human trafficking. 👏❤️ Thank you to each and every person in the room for the depth of your love, care, and support in our mission to #ENDHUMANTRAFFICKING. 

Were you part of this powerhouse event? 🤟Leave a comment and let me know your #1 takeaway! 

#businessmastery #businessowner #businessmindset #entrepreneur #growthmindset #tonyrobbinsbusinessmastery #businesssuccess

node.text:
Opportunities exist everywhere and in every season of life. Sometimes they look like mistakes, or wrong turns, or sweeping disruptions.

It’s important to be able to recognize opportunity, but don’t just wait and see – BE READY. Be PREPARED. Do the work. Then when an opportunity arrives 👊SAY YES. 

Remember — the meeting of PREPARATION and OPPORTUNITY creates the offspring we call “luck.”🍀 

It’s time to ditch your comfort zone and fear of failure and say YES to meaningful opportunities that excite you, give you energy, make you feel alive, connected, excited, and move you in the direction you want to GROW.  

Where is an opportunity lying that you could say YES to today?

#businessmastery #opportunity #businessowner #entrepreneurmindset #growthmindset #successmindset #leadership #opportunityawaits

I AM YOU is a must-watch #film streaming on Amazon and Apple iTunes now! My friend @SoniaNasseryCole is an award-winning Afghan American filmmaker, and the Director and Producer of this profound and deeply moving film. 

There are over 70 million refugees in the world, and half of these are children. It is a life filled with hardship, struggles and uncertainty beyond belief. Sonia’s film, I AM YOU, takes you through the life of three Refugees who leave everything behind and make their way to safety while encountering obstacles that shape their character and their destiny.  

“I Am You is inspired by the story of a refugee, the horrendous conditions before his heroic journey, the heartbreaking indifference confronting him along the way, and the uplifting power and humanity found in hope, truth and justice.” 

Please take a moment to check out I AM YOU on Amazon or iTunes. Once you watch the film, please consider taking a moment to leave a rating of the film and review of your thoughts — this last step will help in Sonia’s mission of spreading knowledge and amplifying voices of those who need to be heard. The more attention we can bring to this cause the more lives we can change together. 🙏🏻❤️ 

🎥 Go to @IAMYOU.film and check out the link in their bio to watch the film.

node.text:
Do you want to know the FASTEST way to END SUFFERING?  

It’s actually very simple... 

Trade your expectations for appreciation and your WHOLE WORLD will change in an instant. 

I truly believe that we’re living in the greatest time in HISTORY — creativity, innovation, and opportunity exist like never before. We’re blessed to live in an abundant time, where so many of our desires are met instantly — at the touch of a button, the click of your mouse, the swipe of your thumb. Social media links us to people all over the world — we can count the number of “friends,” and we get a dopamine boost with every 👍🏻, ❤️, or 😂.

The crazy thing is, that most of us believe that kind of instant gratification = happiness. But what we’re really experiencing when we’re focused on what we GET in life is the ILLUSION of happiness and fulfillment. We live in a culture of EXPECTATION where we are focused on ourselves and our own needs. And when our desires and expectations aren’t met IMMEDIATELY, we feel lack, loss, frustration, rejection…all states of suffering.  

But the TRUTH is, what makes us TRULY happy in life is NOT what we GET, it’s what we GIVE. After all, the secret to living, is giving! 

When we make the choice to focus on appreciation, growth, contribution, and LOVE, we’re making the conscious decision to live in a beautiful state — no matter what.  🙏🏻❤️

Right now, think of something or someone that you’re grateful for and that you can appreciate in THIS moment. Let’s hear from you in the comments — what do you APPRECIATE today?

node.title: The Fastest Way to End Suffering

👥 20,000 Households 
🌍 129 Countries  
💬 7 languages translated simultaneously!  

Here’s a peek inside the room at this past weekend’s Unleash the Power Within Virtual event.  

This event was particularly meaningful as it marked our sixth UPW Virtual in a year! That’s right, our very first UPW in HISTORY came to life last July, and since then we’ve been able to connect with over 1.1 MILLION humans virtually — partners, parents, kids, friends, co-workers, peer groups...and even their four-legged friends! 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 👶👨🏼👩🏾🐶🐈🐠 It’s such an honor to be invited into your kitchens, living rooms, home offices, backyards... and even along for the ride in some of your traveling boat ⛵and van 🚙 adventures! This last year has certainly been unique, and it is such a beautiful and unforgettable experience to connect with you all in such an intimate way.  

The most powerful story is the COMEBACK STORY — where we rise from the ashes and rebuild a life that is truly extraordinary 🔥. A life of MEANING and ULTIMATE FULFILLMENT...on OUR terms. I’m so proud of every single person in the room this past week for showing up, doing the work, and playing full out! 🙌 💥 I can’t wait to see how you will use the tools and strategies to create more joy, more happiness, more LOVE in your lives.

Were you with us this past week, or at any of our Virtual UPWs this year? Drop a comment and let us know — what was one of your biggest takeaways?  

‼️ We also shared something truly exciting — after two full years, our Unleash the Power Within event in November will be ⚡LIVE IN PERSON!⚡ Click the link in my bio for details — I look forward to seeing and serving many of you there!!

On this #MemorialDay, we give thanks as we honor all those who have responded to the call to serve this country — all sons, daughters, mothers, fathers, and countless loved ones who gave all in the name of freedom. 

We send our appreciation and blessings today and every day to all who have served, and send love and prayers to all the families and friends of our fallen heroes. 🇺🇸 

For all soldiers, sailors, airmen and women, and Marines, and every member of our Armed Forces, we are deeply grateful for your courage and dedication to service. 🙏 

Are you honoring the memory of a loved one this Memorial Day? Please share a few words about them in the comments so we can thank them and celebrate their lives.

Video Credit: @usarmy

Traumatic Brain Injury impacts 2 MILLION people every year.  

Quiet Explosions: Healing the Brain, is a powerful documentary by my friend, Emmy Award winning filmmaker Jerri Sher, that shows us how veterans and athletes who have suffered from TBI and PTSD can fully recover — it’s truly miraculous!  

Here’s a heartbreaking statistic — on average, we lose 22 veterans a day to suicide. Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder is truly an invisible illness, one that countless American heroes suffer from in silence.  

To honor #ArmedForcesWeek, Quiet Explosions is available to stream from now until May 28th — tickets include both the full-length documentary, as well as a riveting conversation between filmmaker @jerridga and the brilliant team behind The Brain Warrior's Way podcast, our friends Dr. Amen @doc_amen and Tana Amen. Click the link in my bio to get your ticket.  

If you or someone you know suffers from #TBI or #PTSD, I highly encourage you to watch this documentary, and share it with your friends. These new breakthroughs could help save someone they love.

node.text:
We’re certainly living through unique times. Over the past year and a half, those of us with school-aged children and young adults in our lives have witnessed this generation navigating and evolving in ways they never could have anticipated. 

As we begin to congratulate students for achieving another milestone year completed along their academic path, let us pause for a moment to acknowledge the amount of focus, sacrifice, and hard work — both physical and emotional — it takes to get here. There’s a tremendous amount of pressure to ACHIEVE, and it can be easy to focus on the awards or recognition you didn’t get, the grade you worked for and wanted but didn’t receive, what you don’t have, or what’s missing. This kind of pressure can take a toll on ANYONE, especially our youth.
 
For #mentalhealthactionday, @marisapolvino @katecohendavis @pamroyblog, my partners on the upcoming feature-length film #manssearchformeaning, will premiere a short film about the dangers of high-pressure schooling — the first in their three-part #meaninginmadness docuseries. My friend @prince_ea hosts the one-hour event, on May 20th, which is open and free to everyone. 

If you have students in your life you support, love, and care about, I encourage you to watch this short film. Sign up at: https://straight-up-impact.com/

I’m excited to share that TOMORROW, Tuesday May 11 at 11 AM PT (2 PM Eastern) I’ll be sitting down with my dear friend Dean Graziosi, along with a lineup of incredible guests, for our first-ever OWN YOUR FUTURE Challenge! We’ll be doing 5 days of live trainings from world-class experts for FREE!  

Now that the world is starting to open up again, we all have the opportunity right now to decide what our life is going to look like in the future – and we have to ask ourselves…  

Do we really want to go “back to normal?” Or do we want to create a whole new reality for ourselves? One where we’re in control of our time, finances, and ultimately the IMPACT we can have in our own communities — and the world. 🌎

Over 830,000 of you joined us this past January for my New World New You Challenge where we focused on creating a mindset for success.  This time @deangraziosi and I are teaming up to show you how to create your own economy in this shifting virtual world. We’ll reveal our top strategies to take back control, get creative again after such a tough year, and create a life of true meaning and impact.  
 
If you’re ready to direct and shape your life — to live it on YOUR terms — then this challenge is for YOU! 
 
Remember, if you talk about it, it’s a dream. If you envision it, it’s possible. But if you schedule it, it’s real. Click the link in my bio to register for FREE now, then block May 11 – 15th in your calendar. Looking forward to connecting with you all TOMORROW — see you there!! 🗓️👨🏻‍💻❤️

As a business owner or entrepreneur, it is your opportunity to do more for others than anybody else — in whatever area or industry you’re in.  

It’s about what you GIVE, not what you get.  

And when you’re obsessed with giving more – with meeting and surpassing the needs of your clients, you’ll not only succeed, but you'll make a DIFFERENCE in their lives.  

When you decide to focus on giving instead of getting? You’ll reach more people and touch more lives than ever before – and you’ll GET so much more in return, too. I promise you, when you focus on GIVING and SERVING, you will experience a deeper fulfillment than ever imagined.

The secret to living is giving. ❤️

For all of you business owners, team members, parents, partners, and anyone who provides a service or nurtures a relationship with others, take a moment to consider:  

What business are you REALLY in? How can you FALL IN LOVE with your clients?  

How can we SERVE ONE ANOTHER at the highest level? 

Drop a comment and tell us: What are you really here to GIVE? 🤝❤️

THE SECRET TO LIVING IS GIVING! Our team at @thetonyrobbinsfoundation posted this #TBT photo from one of our Basket Brigades back in the day and I had to share! 

I’ve been feeding families since I was 17 years old — an act inspired by the kindness and generosity my own family was shown when I was 11. Back in 1991 — 30 years ago! — I formalized this approach and The Tony Robbins Foundation was born, built upon the belief that regardless of achievements, financial success, or any other measure of stature, ONLY those who have learned the power of SINCERE and SELFLESS CONTRIBUTION will experience life’s deepest joy; true fulfillment. ❤️🙏🏻

Our Mission is to empower individuals and organizations to STEP UP and make a difference in the quality of life of those often forgotten — our youth, elderly, hungry, homeless, and imprisoned brothers and sisters and ALL who need a boost envisioning a happier way of life.

I am proud to share that in our thirty years of service, The Tony Robbins Foundation has awarded 2,000+ grants and other resources to health and human services organizations, implemented life-changing curriculum in 1,700+ correctional facilities, provided mentorship to thousands of young leaders across the world, and continues to inspire countless individuals to participate in Basket Brigades worldwide. 

Our Foundation continues to fund and partner with innovative, like-minded organizations that are tackling some of our biggest world challenges including finding new food sources to feed billions 🍽️, saving children from human trafficking ⛓️, utilizing state-of-the-art technology to provide shelter for those without homes 🏘️, planting MILLIONS of trees 🌳and creating sustainable farming practices in Africa – and that’s just the start! 

The truth is, even the smallest of gestures make the world a better place. 🌎🤝❤️ How can YOU use your TIME, ENERGY and IDEAS to give a little more today?

node.text:
We ALL have an IDENTITY — a set of BELIEFS that DEFINE who we are, what we can and cannot or WILL not do. And it’s based mostly on our past — some of which is painful, and some pleasurable.

Why is IDENTITY so important to dig under? Because BELIEFS about ourselves are among the strongest forces shaping our lives. BELIEFS control BEHAVIOR.

🌡Here’s a metaphor: You’ve set your life’s thermostat at 72 degrees. That's representative of your personal comfort zone. Note: it’s where you're COMFORTABLE, but NOT your ultimate best self. That 72° is where you are content physically, financially, how much intimacy you’re comfortable with, how connected you feel to your creator, your partner, your friends, your children. If things begin to drop 📉 If you go from a 72 down to a 65, 64, 63, 62… well, something’s gonna kick in! 🧠Your brain is going to say, “Hey! What am I doing down here at a 62°?! I’m more than this!” That’s when your engine kicks on and you begin to get going. 🏃🏻‍♀️🏃🏼

❓Have you ever experienced this? Things got so bad with your health, your body, your relationship, your career, or finances that you hit a threshold and began to do everything you possibly could to make a change?

Unfortunately, the same thing happens on the OTHER side... If you’re a 72°-er and you start doing BETTER than you believe you should — stronger financially, you get in the best shape of your life, deeper relationships, more joy, etc… for most people going from 72 to 88 to 92 degrees, their brain says, “Hey! What are you doing up here?! You’re a 72!” ⁉️ When you’ve achieved BEYOND what you’ve ever dreamed of you’ll feel the engine trip and bring you right back down to where you used to be. A.K.A. self-sabotage.

That's why you don’t need to CHANGE your identity… you need to EXPAND it.💥 In times of growth, our brain MUST be able say, “I AM capable of this!” It's why we do firewalks and board breaking — it’s all a metaphor designed to get you to DO something your brain never believed was possible.

Could you do something today to redefine yourself? Something MORE encompassing of all of you today? Forget your past, who are you NOW? What have you decided to become?

node.text:
Woolly Mammoths will walk the earth again! 🦣

Congratulations to co-founders Ben Lamm, George Church, Ph.D. and their entire team – including leaders in bioethics, genomics, chemical engineering, biotechnology, molecular genetics, and software along with groundbreaking entrepreneurs, inventors and investors –  on today’s launch of COLOSSAL, a new bioscience and genetics company focused on pioneering animal de-extinction technology.  

I have followed the ground-breaking work of Dr. Church for years and have invested in another company with Ben when he founded Hypergiant, an A.I. company focused on developing technology to solve some of the world’s biggest challenges in space, defense, and critical infrastructure. These two are a total powerhouse team, who with the support of the groundbreaking entrepreneurs, inventors, and investors behind them, will radically shift our understanding of modern genetics while developing innovative technologies that not only help bring back extinct species and habitats but advance the entire industry as we know it.  

@itiscolossal is using breakthrough advances in genetic engineering to approach climate change and extinction with innovative and industry-disrupting technology, taking MASSIVE steps to help restore lost ecosystems and ensure a beautiful, habitable planet for generations to come.  

An estimated 1 MILLION animals, plants, and fungi are in danger of extinction – many within a decade. Our team at Colossal hopes that in bringing back critical, lost habitats and ecosystems, we have the potential to halt – and even REVERSE – the effects of climate change. Restoring the woolly mammoth alone has the potential to revitalize the Arctic grasslands, which has major climate change-combatting properties including carbon sequestering, methane suppression and light reflection. Absolutely BRILLIANT!  

Congratulations again, team! It’s a beautiful journey to work together in restoring and caring for this beautiful blue planet we all call home 💙🌎.

Today marks the 20th anniversary of the September 11th terrorist attacks that took the lives of nearly 3,000 men, women, and children leaving thousands of families — and our nation — reeling from shock, grief, pain & heartbreak beyond imagination.

On this day we have vowed to #neverforget, let us look back and remember the remarkable courage, beautiful acts of compassion between strangers, and the powerful resilience of the human spirit that guides and lifts us through our darkest of hours.

Let us remember the bravery and selflessness of our first responders who ran into crumbling buildings, blazing fires, and total chaos risking their lives to save others. Many made the ultimate sacrifice that day. We honor you.

Let us remember the countless heroes – pilots, flight attendants, passengers, military, doctors, nurses, Pentagon and World Trade Center workers, animal rescue teams, guide and rescue dogs, by-standers, and ALL who played a part in saving as many lives as possible. We send our deepest gratitude to you, and to those who continue to nurture the healing of those still living with pain and trauma.

Let us remember the spirit of unity that brought us together from all backgrounds & walks of life, united in our common humanity. We reflect on the countless acts of kindness that demonstrate the triumph of love. 

We remember those we lost & pray for their mothers, fathers, brothers, sisters, children, friends & all whose hearts they touched. As we think of the many heart-wrenching goodbye calls made to loved ones, we understand this truth: that in the end, LOVE is all that truly matters. It is our greatest gift, our highest purpose, & the legacy of those we lost.

We were so touched by this beautiful tribute for the @911memorial #NeverForgetFund. To see the full video & support their important work, please visit 911memorial.org/20th-anniversary.

Through and in it all, we take comfort knowing that the light of the human heart & spirit cannot be extinguished.

On 9/11 I was leading an event with 2,500 people — many had lost loved ones that morning. Click the link in bio if you’d like to see the learnings & healings from that day.

#NeverForget911

One of the most sacred gifts that we can offer one another is our labor. ❤️💪🏼 When we give our labor, what we’re really giving is ourselves. Our work is an expression of our energy, our creativity, our passion, and our JOY. Ultimately, our work is our LOVE in ACTION and a sharing and offering of our most precious gift of life itself. 

This Labor Day weekend, we are sending our deepest gratitude for the gift of labor in all forms. To our teachers, healthcare workers, brothers and sisters in the armed forces, and to all who labor in countless professions, shops, factories, farms and fields, restaurants, those who care for our elders, who nurture families from home – thank you for your love and dedication. To those who have retired, we thank you for a lifetime of giving from your hands and heart. All that we contribute in service to each other has a ripple effect that reaches and touches the world around us, and we are deeply grateful for you all!  

🙏🏼❤️ Wherever you are in the world today, I invite you to take a moment to ask yourself... how can you find a sense of joy and fulfillment in your daily work? How does YOUR labor (at work, school, home, or otherwise) play a part in the bigger picture of CONTRIBUTION and SERVICE to life? How is your labor your GIFT to others?   

Thank you for your beautiful contributions to our world — we honor you! 🙏🏼 

#labordayweekend #laborday #loveinaction #laborday2021

Remember — the meeting of PREPARATION and OPPORTUNITY creates the offspring we call “luck.”🍀 

It’s time to ditch your comfort zone and fear of failure and say YES to meaningful opportunities that excite you, give you energy, make you feel alive, connected, excited, and move you in the direction you want to GROW.  

Where is an opportunity lying that you could say YES to today?

Belly rubs for all our furry friends out there on this National Dog Day today. 🐶 We sure love our dog — she's part of the family! — and we know you love yours too, so we thought we'd share a quick insight from our dear friend and our girl's personal trainer, Los Angeles based 👉Tamar Geller, of The Loved Dog @theloveddog.

What we love most about Tamar’s unique dog training method and why we entrust our doggie to her is because Tamar’s core principles for teaching dogs are aligned with our core principles for teaching humans. 

Tamar believes (and we do too!) that a big part of the connection we humans share with dogs is because we actually have so much in common. We all require essentially the same BASIC NEEDS. Just like you have heard while attending any of Tony's seminars, the 6 Human Needs are: Certainty, Variety, Love & Connection, Significance, Growth, and Contribution. 

And just like us human creatures, dogs also naturally move AWAY from PAIN ⛔️and🚦TOWARDS PLEASURE.

Tamar urges dog lovers to make sure every pup has what they need to feel loved, safe, active, learning, growing, and engaged. We keep them happy and healthy by meeting their core needs...

Take Certainty for example, we pup parents create a safe environment for our doggos by providing predictability -- a sturdy routine is a very welcomed thing in the daily life of a dog.

BUT, just like us, too much predictability and dogs get bored! And when we aren't giving them enough Variety, they create their own to meet the need by digging, chewing, or as Tamar calls it, "arts and crafts projects" like unrolling all the toilet paper or emptying the trash can.🙈🙊🙉 

And remember, just like us, each dog’s needs fall in a unique order. So, what brings dogs the most happiness is unique to each pup. For some it might be going outside to play, for others it might be curling up on your bed, and others still, it's food!

Connect with your dog today, get present with them, and learn the best ways to meet their unique needs and reciprocate the love! ❤️🐕🐩🦮🐕‍🦺

#NationalDogDay #TheLovedDog #NeedsPsychology

What a pleasure it was to welcome John Foley, CEO and Founder of @onepeloton, to speak at our recent Business Mastery program!

Business Mastery happens just twice a year – it’s five full days and nights of business bootcamp! Business owners and entrepreneurs from all over the world representing every level and niche – from nine-figure corporations to mom-and-pop start-ups – get together to learn how to take their businesses to the next level. 📈

One of the highlights of our program is the opportunity to hear directly from some of the most successful, strategic, wicked smart industry disrupters of our time. 👊🔥😎 I love to bring on brilliant business minds who embody the true spirit of what it means to be an entrepreneur – people who started with nothing but a vision and fought through every obstacle imaginable to bring their vision to life.  

Most people know John as the founder and CEO of #Peloton, the $32 BILLION at-home exercise phenomenon that over 1 MILLION people train on daily! But behind this seemingly overnight success is a story of perseverance, unwavering commitment, and VISION to create something BIG that would completely change the industry. 

Today, Peloton has 5.4 million raving fans, and John has created an online community that both supports and challenges people to live healthier lives. His dedication to principles like “stay hungry and humble” and “don’t use hope as a method” are part of the secret to his success.  

I’m thrilled to be able to share the full interview with you all – just click the link in my bio to listen! You’ll hear part of John’s story, and learn how he and his team built Peloton to be the powerhouse it is today – even after facing rejection and hearing NO over 400 times!! 🤯👏

Thank you, John, it was a privilege to have you speak with us at Business Mastery! You have such a beautiful heart and mind. 🙏❤️ I look forward to our next meeting! And for those of you who will be joining us for our upcoming Business Mastery Virtual in just a couple of weeks, I’ll see you soon!

#pelotonbike #podcast #tonyrobbinspodcast #businesssuccess #successmindset #businessowner #entrepreneur
